## Feature 2: Robust Dual-Engine AI Fallback System
This unique architectural feature ensures the application never crashes if Google's API goes offline.

### 2.1 Use Case Diagram (AI Fault Tolerance)
```mermaid
usecaseDiagram
    actor BackendAPI as Express Backend
    
    usecase "Route AI Request" as Route
    usecase "Try Google Gemini" as TryG
    usecase "Try OpenAI ChatGPT" as TryO
    usecase "Trigger Fallback Alert" as Alert
    
    BackendAPI --> Route
    Route ..> TryG : Primary Attempt
    TryG ..> TryO : <<extend>> (If TimeOut/429)
    TryO ..> Alert : <<extend>> (If Both Fail)
```

### 2.2 Sequence Diagram (Failover Protocol)
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Feature as Any AI Feature
    participant Fallback as generateWithFallback()
    participant DB as engine_config
    participant Gemini as Google API
    participant OpenAI as ChatGPT API

    Feature->>Fallback: Request Generation
    Fallback->>DB: SELECT status FROM ai_models
    Fallback->>Gemini: model.generateContent()
    alt Throw 500/429 Error
        Gemini--xFallback: Connection Timeout
        Fallback->>DB: Fetch OPENAI_API_KEY
        Fallback->>OpenAI: chat.completions.create()
        OpenAI-->>Fallback: Recovery Success
    end
    Fallback-->>Feature: Seamless Response
```

